    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Romans",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Man is not justified by the law of Moses\u2014He is justified through righteousness, which comes through faith in Christ, made possible through Christ's atoning sacrifice.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "What advantage then hath the Jew? or what profit is there of circumcision?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 3:1\u20132 What advantage then hath the Jew over the Gentile? or what profit of circumcision, who is not a Jew from the heart? But he who is a Jew from the heart, I say hath much every way\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0preeminence.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Much every way: chiefly, because that unto them were committed the oracles of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:38; 2\u00a0Ne. 29:4 (4\u20136).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 8:28 (26\u201328).",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0May it not be!",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 30:42 (37\u201342).",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 51:4.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say? Is God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 3:5\u20138 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0recommend.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 26:7; Alma 42:1 (1, 13\u201325).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0May it not be!",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory; why yet am I also judged as a sinner?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0in, by, because of.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And not rather, (as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? whose damnation is just.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Damnation.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 133
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "What then? are we better than they? No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 14:2\u20133; 53:1 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They are all gone out of the way, they are together become unprofitable; there is none that doeth good, no, not one.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 82:6.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 17:10 (7\u201310); Mosiah 2:21 (20\u201321).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 33:4; 35:12.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Their throat is an open sepulchre; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps is under their lips:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 5:9.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 140:3 (1\u201313).",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1420
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 41:11; Morm. 8:31.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their feet are swift to shed blood:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 59:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Destruction and misery are in their ways:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:25; Morm. 8:38.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the way of peace have they not known:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 20:22 (18\u201322).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no fear of God before their eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:56 (55\u201356).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now we know that what things soever the law saith, it saith to them who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:63.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guilt.",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore by the deeds of the law there shall no flesh be justified in his sight: for by the law is the knowledge of sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 25:23.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Law of Moses.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 2:5 (5\u20138).",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0through.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested, being witnessed by the law and the prophets;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0apart from, without intervention of.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Even the righteousness of God which is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:9; 1\u00a0Ne. 10:6. TG\u00a0Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn; Sin.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 3:24 Therefore being justified only by his grace\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 20:30.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whom God hath set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0purposed, designed beforehand.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0mercy seat. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Redemption.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blood, Symbolism of.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Remission of Sins.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To declare, I say, at this time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of him which believeth in Jesus.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Justice of.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what law? of works? Nay: but by the law of faith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 26:36 (10\u201312, 36); D&C 3:4; 84:73.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore we conclude that a man is justified by faith without the deeds of the law.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Justification.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0apart from, without intervention of.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Is he the God of the Jews only? is he not also of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 30:2 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gentiles.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Seeing it is one God, which shall justify the circumcision by faith, and uncircumcision through faith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 2:5; D&C 121:28.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Do we then make void the law through faith? God forbid: yea, we establish the law.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0May it not be!",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0but.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}